posts.title: Grand Opening... Grand Closing!
posts.content:
I work freelance gigs. Which operate in the manner of a film shoot: a manager will be hired for a short contract-- & will then 'crew up' by filling a list of job roles with other freelancers. Some have worked-together before, some haven't-- but as long as everyone understands the routine of these-sorts-of-gigs-- we can function as a team.

Over the last year or 2-- one small company has hired a series of black women as the manager. A specific sort of black woman. Like when you watch news about Chicago and you saw former mayor Lori Lightfoot. Or that clumsy prosecutor Kim Foxx in the Jussie Smollet case. Or some ghetto-ass city council meeting where people "axe" questions and shout. I'm not talking about flashy blacks-- like Tiffany Henyard (the "super mayor") of Dalton, IL. These are shabby looking women who look like they're in line for welfare benefits, or crying on the local news because their gangsta son Lil Poo-Poo got shot.

I saw the same thing happen several times: new blackgurl manager with a weird pseudo-african first name is hired. She claims to have a ton of experience. But she has trouble with the usual workflow. 'That's not how I do it' she insists. Ok-- but how She Does It-- was at some low rent all-black job in the ghetto. Where a paper bag full of apples and little cartons of chocolate milk were considered an acceptable 'crew meal' for adults. Where some of the working men were drunk or high every day, some were perpetually late or no-shows, where they need to be supervised like children/ and they're happier when they ARE supervised like children.

So then the gurl clashes-with the non-ghetto crew. And she interpets their pushback as "these racist whites are not respecting my authority. I have to try to dominate them by being a bitch." (they don't have to be white. that's still how she reacts).

As the days progress-- she starts fucking-up in obvious ways. And rather than admit it so the problems can be fixed... she generates a flurry of excuses, denials, diversions, obfuscations-- and AWOL silences. Everybody realizes she's A Problem-- and compartmentalizes her, to minimize damage. Others pick up the slack & do the things she was hired to do as-best-as-possible. And she rides-it-out in irrelevance, never to be rehired.

I just came-off a small 2-day gig. This time-- this new gurl-- Brought The Ghetto With Her. She disregarded the recommended list of reliable crew-- and hired a crew of ghetto guys she knew personally from who-knows-where. A full size desk stapler-- which we REALLY needed, to staple a pile of 25 contracts-- went missing. Some doofus had put it in his pocket & wandered off. I don't even think he was stealing it. When it came time to Strike our makeshift office... I offered him the stapler & some Sharpie markers... and he lit-up like no one had ever given him anything in his life.

Another one was visibly afraid-- when he & I had to run an errand-- & I hailed a cab rather than taking the subway. I don't know if he thought I'd make him pay half the fare/ or if he'd be yelled-at for spending money. He was highly skeptical that getting to our destination fast was more important than saving ten bucks. He only believed I had the authority to make that judgement call- when I showed him I have a company credit card to charge the ride.

I'm digressing into every-little-detail... as I process what felt 'off'...

But the simple fact is... I woke up feeling scuzzy this morning. Like- the urge to scrub extra-hard in the shower.

I don't want to work in the fucking ghetto. What's the opposite of "Gentrification"? My job was overrun by Ghettofication, for a couple days. This manager gurl won't be rehired. I will never see her Wack Pack of hapless dudes again. I don't know if the company has learned their lesson yet. I definitely understand why MLK Jr. & Louis Farrakhan both told their congregations to wear suits and practice Respectability. And why that has been so hard for them to achieve. I understand why Jesse Lee Peterson believes the things he does.
